<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000038#     2#         1374#">Va. Code Ann. § 38.2-1374</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_38.2-1374"/><heading><desig>§ 38.2-1374.</desig><title>Minimum reserves</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a"/><heading><desig>A.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> In no event shall an insurer's aggregate reserves for all life insurance policies, excluding disability and accidental death benefits, be less than the aggregate reserves calculated in accordance with the methods set forth in <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 38.2-1372"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 38.2-1372">§§ 38.2-1372<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000038#     2#         1372#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 38.2-1373"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 38.2-1373">38.2-1373<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000038#     2#         1373#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 38.2-1376"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 38.2-1376">38.2-1376<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000038#     2#         1376#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, and <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 38.2-1377"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 38.2-1377">38.2-1377<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000038#     2#         1377#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> and the mortality table or tables and rate or rates of interest used in calculating nonforfeiture benefits for those policies.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_b"/><heading><desig>B.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> In no event shall the aggregate reserves for all policies, contracts, and benefits be less than the aggregate reserves determined by the appointed actuary to be necessary to render the opinion required by <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 38.2-1367"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 38.2-1367">§ 38.2-1367<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000038#     2#         1367#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p><citation normalizedCite="2014 VA CH 571"><content><span normalizedCite="2014 Va. Ch. 571">2014, c. 571<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2014#000571#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativeDocBody><metadata><dc:metadata xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><dc:identifier identifierScheme="PGUID">urn:contentItem:5K0Y-PWB0-004G-K1WB-00000-00</dc:identifier><dc:source sourceScheme="productContentSetIdentifier">10816</dc:source><dc:date dateType="last-updated">2016-06-15</dc:date></dc:metadata><publicationInfo><publicationName>CODE OF VIRGINIA </publicationName><copyright>Copyright © 2016  by Matthew Bender &amp; Company, Inc. a member of the LexisNexis Group. All rights reserved</copyright></publicationInfo><hierarchy><hierarchyLevel levelType="title"><heading><desi